{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/sepsis/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"b93e807a-0902-5c86-be52-22d6b24c8c21","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 3cdc8464-6651-4710-ad32-aa0600a5693f --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 3cdc8464-6651-4710-ad32-aa0600a5693f -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 257f3384-fdcf-4d71-9809-aa0600a5693f --><!-- begin field dac14ea3-a017-4e25-86bf-aa0600a5693f --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field dac14ea3-a017-4e25-86bf-aa0600a5693f --><!-- begin field 735015f3-163c-4535-8e76-aa0600a5693f --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 735015f3-163c-4535-8e76-aa0600a5693f --><!-- begin field 3bbf5f92-d6da-4eb2-9fa0-aa0600a5693f --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 3bbf5f92-d6da-4eb2-9fa0-aa0600a5693f --><!-- begin field 59ba4b3f-24d1-4cef-b455-aa0600a5693f --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 59ba4b3f-24d1-4cef-b455-aa0600a5693f --><!-- begin field 6f530453-aa71-4fee-a6ce-aa0600a5693f --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field 6f530453-aa71-4fee-a6ce-aa0600a5693f --><!-- begin field 19c71d81-1a73-43ba-a86e-aa0600a5693f --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 19c71d81-1a73-43ba-a86e-aa0600a5693f --><!-- end item 257f3384-fdcf-4d71-9809-aa0600a5693f -->","topic":{"id":"6934ac75-4c45-5f2f-8c9a-2d8851f1adf5","topicId":"eab5610a-80e3-49d5-ac25-aa0600a5625f","topicName":"Sepsis","slug":"sepsis","lastRevised":"Last revised in April 2020","chapters":[{"id":"21403d5c-7f6a-58f8-a754-f80facfcc7b7","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"01bfd22f-a788-595c-9d77-4f15e7d21471","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"8280962c-6cb2-53a1-8eed-ec18c19db62a","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"02ea2408-9b6e-5954-a3bc-8305ad7c2b3d","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"c2a838a7-45f2-5a2b-8e94-13f83b057517","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"a1a6b520-0d3e-5568-8fcf-e882ce604048","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"a9d2a1af-b338-5209-93b4-bddc7b6b5cbd","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"b2606ff0-0e97-55b2-83e3-4b0c5d0a2be2","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"3c4a84a7-c8f8-551b-bf15-639adaa8882d","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"af6a0131-ac1